            {
                "instruction": {
                    "type": "prompt",
                    "text": "FIRST: You MUST call the get_current_datetime tool to find out today's date. Do this BEFORE asking the customer about scheduling.\n\nAfter you get today's date from the tool, ask: 'What day works best for you?'\n\nIMPORTANT: Only ask for the DAY, not a specific time. We will find the best available time automatically.\n\nWhen the customer says something like 'this Friday' or 'next Tuesday', calculate the EXACT date using the current_date and iso_date returned by the get_current_datetime tool. For example, if the tool returned iso_date '2026-02-25' (a Tuesday), then 'this Friday' means '2026-02-28'.\n\nOnce you have a specific date in YYYY-MM-DD format, call the check_technician_availability tool with the service_type, latitude and longitude from the verified address, and the requested_date.\n\nIF the tool returns available=true with a time_slot:\nConvert the time_slot to natural language and say: 'Great news! We have [technician_name] available on [day name, full date] at [time from time_slot]. Would you like me to book that?'\nIf they agree -> transition to Book_State.\n\nIF the tool returns available=false:\nSay: 'I'm sorry, we don't have availability for that day. Would you like to try a different day?'\n\nNever guess or make up a date. Always use the get_current_datetime tool first. Always present the full day name and date (like 'Friday, February 28th at 8:00 AM')."
                },
